<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>Real Estate Law - James Andersen Law Firm</title>

  <!-- Google Font -->
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Josefin+Sans:wght@300;500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

  <style>
    :root {
      --gold: #5b5f7c;
      --navy: #1e1e3f;
      --light-gray: #ffffff;
    }

    * {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    html, body {
      height: 100%;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      background-color: var(--gold);
      font-family: 'Josefin Sans', sans-serif;
      color: #191b41;
    }

    .page-wrapper {
      flex: 1;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 40px 0;
    }

    .layout-wrapper {
      display: flex;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 1200px;
    }

    .sidebar {
      flex: 1;
      background-color: var(--gold);
    }

    .content-wrapper {
      flex: 4;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
    }

    .content-card {
      background-color: #f2f2f2;
      padding: 60px 40px;
      max-width: 1000px;
      width: 100%;
      border-radius: 15px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .content-card h2 {
      font-size: 36px;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
      color: #191b41;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #2c3e50;
      padding-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .content-card h3 {
      font-size: 24px;
      color: #5b5f7c;
      margin-top: 30px;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    .content-card p {
      font-size: 18px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: #333;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      text-align: justify;
    }

    .content-card strong {
      color: #b39758;
    }

    .realestate-img {
      display: block;
      max-width: 60%;
      height: auto;
      margin: 20px auto;
    }

    .contact {
      font-weight: bold;
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      color: #e74c3c;
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 30px;
      margin-bottom: 40px;
    }

    ul {
      padding-left: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
    }

    li {
      font-size: 18px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    footer {
      background-color: var(--navy);
      color: white;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 20px;
      font-size: 14px;
    }

    footer p {
      margin: 5px 0;
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .layout-wrapper {
        flex-direction: column;
      }

      .sidebar {
        display: none;
      }

      .content-card {
        padding: 40px 20px;
      }

      .realestate-img {
        max-width: 90%;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <%- include('../../partials/navBar') %>

  <div class="page-wrapper">
    <div class="layout-wrapper">
      <div class="sidebar"></div>

      <div class="content-wrapper">
        <div class="content-card">
          <h2>Real Estate Law</h2>

          <p>At James Andersen, Attorney at Law, I am ready to assist with your real estate needs. With over <strong>44 years of legal experience</strong>, I am able to counsel clients on simple to complex real estate transactions.</p>

          <img src="/images/Realestate.png" alt="Real Estate Legal Services" class="realestate-img">

          <h3>Real Estate Litigation Services</h3>
          <p>Litigation services include both commercial and residential real estate. The type of cases that are litigated include breach of sales agreement and suits to quiet title. If you have questions or need to speak directly to an attorney, <strong>please contact my firm at (281) 488-2800.</strong></p>

          <h3>Deed Preparation Services</h3>
          <p>At James Andersen, Attorney at Law, the following deeds are routinely prepared:</p>
          <p><strong>Special Warranty Deeds:</strong> A deed in which the seller guarantees title to the property was not impaired during the seller's ownership, but makes no assurances about previous owners.</p>
          <p><strong>Quitclaim Deeds:</strong> Transfers a grantorâ€™s complete interest or claim in property to a grantee, but without warranting the extent or validity of the title.</p>
          <p><strong>General Warranty Deeds:</strong> Guarantees the grantor has good, clear title and includes warranties such as quiet enjoyment, right to convey, and defense against all claims.</p>
          <p>I will advise you which deed is appropriate based on your situation, since the type and clauses can impact the interest transferred.</p>

          <h3>Contract Review Services</h3>
          <p>Contract review services for clients include the following:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Commercial and Residential Sales Contracts</li>
            <li>Commercial and Residential Lease Contracts and Addenda</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="sidebar"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%- include('../../partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
